The election commencement time for the family trust election: Enter the commencement date (day, month, year) for the Family Trust election or the effective date (day, month, year) of a variation by way of an order, an agreement or an award. This should only be completed if: - specifying the full income year eg. 2007-2008 and if the family control in section 272-87 of Schedule 2F to ITAA 1936 has not been satisfied at all times during the specified full income year eg. 2007-2008 from the day specified for an election to be made. In these circumstances, the election commencement time will be the later of the earliest time from which the family control test was passed continuously until the end of the full income year eg. 2007-2008 and the beginning of the day specified for an election to be made, or - varying the specified individual of a family trust election under subsection 272-80(5C) of Schedule 2F to the ITAA 1936 as a result of an order, an agreement, or an award. The variation effective date is the variation date specified by the order, agreement or award.
The election commencement time for the family trust election or effective date of a variation

Income year specified for the purposes of the family trust election: Enter the four-digit income year (2005 and later) specified for the purposes of the Family Trust election. Where varying the specified individual of a family trust election, other than by way of an order, an agreement or an award write the four-digit, current income year of the trusts return of income with which the variation must be lodged. The variation effective date is the first day of that year of income or the commencement date of the original election, whichever is later. Where revoking a current election, specify the income year exactly as provided previously in the relevant family trust election.
Income year specified for the purposes of the family trust election or revocation

The income year for which the details of the election being revoked were included in the tax return for the trust or given to the Commissioner: Enter the income year for which the details of the election being revoked were included in the tax return for the trust or given to the Commissioner. The income year for which the details of the election being revoked were included in the tax return for the trust or given to the Commissioner as required under subsection 272-80(2) of Schedule 2F to the ITAA 1936 or sub-items 22(4) or 22A(4) of Schedule 1 to the Taxation Laws Amendment (Trust Loss and Other Deductions) Act 1998.
